{
  "texts": [
    "Here comes the role of topic modeling feature.",
    "Recently, topic modeling grabbed attention of researchers, particularly using matrix factorization and probabilistic modeling approaches.",
    "Latent dirichlet allocation (LDA) is a widely used probabilistic model for topic modeling that was introduced by Blei et al. [16] in 2003.",
    "LDA represents each document as a mixture of latent topics and represents each topic as a probability distribution over the words in the vocabulary.",
    "The goal of LDA is to learn the latent topics and their associated word distributions from the corpus of documents."
  ]
}